# ==============================================================================
# NOTES FOR TEAM COLLABORATION
# ==============================================================================

# IMPORTANT: This .gitignore file helps protect sensitive information.
# 
# Files that SHOULD be committed:
# - All .tf files (main.tf, variables.tf, outputs.tf, versions.tf)
# - terraform.tfvars.example (template file)
# - README.md and documentation
# - Python function source code
# - requirements.txt
# 
# Files that should NEVER be committed:
# - terraform.tfvars (contains sensitive passwords and emails)
# - *.tfstate files (contain infrastructure state and secrets)
# - Service account JSON key files
# - Any files with actual passwords or credentials
# 
# Best practices:
# 1. Always review files before committing with 'git diff --cached'
# 2. Use 'git status' to verify only intended files are staged
# 3. Consider using 'git secrets' or similar tools for additional protection
# 4. Regularly audit repository for accidentally committed secrets